<subSubSection id="C793654A0504FFBCFF0B6E92FED79161" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph id="8F3636C10504FFBDFF0B6E92FDD19726" blockId="2.[151,1437,1447,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
On the night of 
<date id="FB3710010504FFBDFECF6E92FDEE95E2" box="[339,550,1447,1473]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" value="2010-09-07">7 September 2010</date>
, a male specimen resembling 
<taxonomicName id="48894D420504FFBDFC1F6E92FBC595E2" authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[899,1037,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perloides">
<emphasis id="BDFDEAD30504FFBDFC1F6E92FBC595E2" box="[899,1037,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. perloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-according to the descriptions and illustrations in 
<bibRefCitation id="EB184B300504FFBDFEDF6EFEFE2695C6" author="Guenee, A." box="[323,494,1482,1509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" refId="ref8454" refString="Guenee, A. (1852 - 1854) Noctuelites (II). In: Boisduval, J. A. &amp; Guenee, A., Histoire naturelle des lnsectes. Species general des Lepidopteres. Vol. 6. Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret, Paris, pp. 29. [nº 30]" type="journal volume" year="1852">Guenée (1852)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EB184B300504FFBDFE606EFEFD6B95C6" author="Rambur, P." box="[508,675,1482,1509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" refId="ref8875" refString="Rambur, P. (1858 - [1866]) Catalogue systematique des Lepidopteres d'Andalousie. Bailliere, Paris. 412 pp." type="book" year="1858">Rambur (1858</bibRefCitation>
-[1866]) and Culot (1909-1913)- was photographed by Penny Hale at Finca La Molina, Casares, Málaga, 
<collectingCountry id="F79E76510504FFBDFDD26EDAFD46962A" box="[590,654,1519,1545]" name="Spain" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Spain</collectingCountry>
(30STF93) (
<figureCitation id="17B22A440504FFBDFCBF6EDAFCB89629" box="[803,880,1519,1546]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1832,1856]" captionTargetBox="[201,1390,200,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-28@4.[184,1404,181,1808]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. 1a. Syntype of Bryophila perloides. Designated here as lectotype.Andalusia, Spain. NHMUK. 1b. Bryophila perloides. Male, Finca La Molina, Casares, Málaga, Andalusia, Spain (Photo Penny Hale). 1c. Bryophila perloides. Male, Campo de Gibraltar, Algeciras, Cádiz, Spain (Photo José Manuel Gaona Ríos). 1d. Bryophila perloides. Male, Campo de Gibraltar, Algeciras, Cádiz, Spain (Photo José Manuel Gaona Ríos). 1e. Bryopsis muralis. Male, Germany. HNHM. 1f. Bryopsis muralis. Female, Germany. HNHM. 1g. Nyctobrya simonyi. Male, Tenerife, Canary Islands, Spain. NHMW. 1h. Nyctobrya simonyi. Female, Tenerife, Canary Islands, Spain. NHMW." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406314/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Fig 1b</figureCitation>
). Following the suggestion of MF, the specimen was retained and sent to him for dissection. Examining the picture of the moth, JLY suggested 
<taxonomicName id="48894D420504FFBDFB7B6D26FAB9960E" authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[1255,1393,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perloides">
<emphasis id="BDFDEAD30504FFBDFB7B6D26FAB9960E" box="[1255,1393,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. perloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an assumption shared by the rest of the team and confirmed by genitalia examination (
<figureCitation id="17B22A440504FFBDFBD56D02FB5E9671" box="[1097,1174,1591,1618]" captionStart="FIGURE 6. 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[239,1379,231,1767]" captionTargetId="figure-28@10.[159,1429,181,1875]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. 6a. Male genitalia of Bryophila perloides, male, Finca La Molina, Casares, Málaga, Andalusia. Genit, prep. MF, ZMC. 6b. Genitalia of the syntype of Bryophila perloides, designated here as lectotype. Andalusia, Spain. Genit, prep. Gyula M. László, NHMUK, specimen labelled as 010918082. 6c. Male genitalia of Bryophila barbaria. Lectotype male, High Atlas Mts, Morocco. Slide No.: RL12477. NHMW." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406328" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406328/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Fig 6a</figureCitation>
). The genitalia showed crucial differences from those of 
<taxonomicName id="48894D420504FFBDFD916D6EFD3F9656" authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Treitschke" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Corley" baseAuthorityYear="2015" box="[525,759,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="domestica">
<emphasis id="BDFDEAD30504FFBDFD916D6EFD3F9656" box="[525,759,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Bryophila domestica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EB184B300504FFBDFCFE6D6EFBFB9656" author="Fibiger, M. &amp; Ronkay, L. &amp; Steiner, A. &amp; Zilli, A." box="[866,1075,1627,1653]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" refId="ref8188" refString="Fibiger, M., Ronkay, L., Steiner, A. &amp; Zilli, A. (2009) Noctuidae Europaeae. Vol. 11. Pantheinae, Dilobinae, Acronictinae, Eustrotiinae, Nolinae, Bagisarinae, Acontiinae, Metoponiinae, Heliothinae and Bryophilinae. Entomological Press, Soro, 504 pp." type="book" year="2009">
Fibiger 
<emphasis id="BDFDEAD30504FFBDFC276D6EFC249656" box="[955,1004,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="17B22A440504FFBDFBF66D6EFB799656" box="[1130,1201,1626,1653]" captionStart="FIGURE 5. 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[281,1304,247,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[155,1432,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. 5a. Male genitalia of Bryophila domestica, as figured in Noctuidae Europaeae, vol. 11 (Fibiger et al., 2009). 5b. Male genitalia of Bryopsis muralis. Slide No.: RL9677, Sardinia, Italy. HNHM. 5c. Male genitalia of Nyctobrya simonyi. Slide No.: VM19488, Tenerife, Canary Islands, Spain. NHMW." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406324/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Fig 5a</figureCitation>
in this paper) and of 
<taxonomicName id="48894D420504FFBDFF0B6D4AFE9F96BA" baseAuthorityName="J.R.Forster" baseAuthorityYear="1771" box="[151,343,1663,1689]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Bryopsidaceae" genus="Bryopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bryopsidales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="muralis">
<emphasis id="BDFDEAD30504FFBDFF0B6D4AFE9F96BA" box="[151,343,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Bryopsis muralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="17B22A440504FFBDFEFA6D4AFE7A96BA" box="[358,434,1662,1689]" captionStart="FIGURE 5. 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[281,1304,247,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[155,1432,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. 5a. Male genitalia of Bryophila domestica, as figured in Noctuidae Europaeae, vol. 11 (Fibiger et al., 2009). 5b. Male genitalia of Bryopsis muralis. Slide No.: RL9677, Sardinia, Italy. HNHM. 5c. Male genitalia of Nyctobrya simonyi. Slide No.: VM19488, Tenerife, Canary Islands, Spain. NHMW." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406324/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Fig 5b</figureCitation>
; for taxonomic nomenclature, see Discussion), although they are much closer to those of 
<taxonomicName id="48894D420504FFBDFF0B6D96FEE1969E" authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Treitschke" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Corley" baseAuthorityYear="2015" box="[151,297,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="domestica">
<emphasis id="BDFDEAD30504FFBDFF0B6D96FEE1969E" box="[151,297,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. domestica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by the much shorter central claspers, wider and cygnated uncus and epiphallus broader and without distal spicules. The genitalia of one of the 
<typeStatus id="503288630504FFBDFCFD6DF2FC0B96C2" box="[865,963,1735,1761]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="48894D420504FFBDFC756DF2FBB996C2" authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[1001,1137,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perloides">
<emphasis id="BDFDEAD30504FFBDFC756DF2FBB996C2" box="[1001,1137,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. perloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
